snippet.textDisplay:
Hello Shaq,
Here is an email I sent my little brother today. His birthday is 8-24-84 My initials are KO. I have been asking for help without success for far too long now. My emotional state has been in too poor of a state for too long considering that my Message, my path to Healing has long been documented and I have given healing advice to hundreds within Hollywood and Pro Athletes around the World. I should be in a better state I want to know why I have yet to see my healing words put into action to those I have shared them with and beyond. Are they recording my every word and action but restricting my Healing words from those they are intended for? I believe so. That is absolutely unacceptable and needs to be corrected immediately. If I gave anyone healing advice that is my wisdom for them to use and share however they desire. I don't ever say anything new regarding Healing, it is all repeated, my Healing message has long been completed. My initials are KO. I have been asking for help without success for far too long now. My emotional state has been in too poor of a state for too long considering that my message, my path to Healing has long been documented and I have given healing advice to hundreds within Hollywood and Pro Athletes around the World. I should be in a better state I want to know why I have yet to see my healing words put into action to those I have shared them with and beyond. Are they recording my every word and action but restricting my Healing words from those they are intended for. That is absolutely unacceptable and needs to be corrected immediately. If I gave anyone healing advice that is my wisdom for them to use and share however they desire. I don't ever say anything new regarding Healing, it is all repeated, my Healing message has long been completed.

To my Brother,
I am sorry about Kobe, I know that hurt your Heart. I’m very sorry that he is gone. He left the world a ton of personal inspiring videos to always continue to motivate future generations & to remember him from.

I was at Knotts listening to “Talking to Myself” by Eminem featuring a singer named Kobe right before I found out he died. I was angry on the roller coaster and the song felt wrong in tempo but fitting in the title. I’m doing the best I can but I am very sensitive to noise and get distracted very often. I get lost & distracted in thought very often. My brain is very advanced but severely lacks challenges. I’m going through drastic changes and cannot find anyone that knows how to help me.

I don’t blame anyone I just want you to know I’m not able to support anyone in our family because of what I am going through and nobody understands. Because nobody understands what I am going through they get confused and uncomfortable in disbelief so I keep to myself. I never saw Aunt Juli the entire time I was outside, or my dog. That hurts my Heart beyond words.

I’m sorry Casey, Kobe was a beautiful piece of God’s art. Beautiful!
Everything in life happens for a reason, 💯.
Kobe Bryant will be remembered and honored through the intense passionate examples from myself and others for generations.
Gotta find my Black Mamba mentality, Son!
Love Kyle
